name: Da Funk
wikiSummary: "Da Funk" is an instrumental track by Daft Punk included on their debut album Homework. It was initially released as a single in 1995 under the Soma Quality Recordings label and again in late 1996 after the band signed with Virgin Records. The single included the B-side "Musique", a track that later appeared in the album Musique Vol. 1 1993-2005. "Da Funk" and its accompanying video directed by Spike Jonze are considered classics of 1990s house music.
wikiText:
"Da Funk" is an instrumental track by Daft Punk included on their debut album Homework. It was initially released as a single in 1995 under the Soma Quality Recordings label and again in late 1996 after the band signed with Virgin Records. The single included the B-side "Musique", a track that later appeared in the album Musique Vol. 1 1993-2005. "Da Funk" and its accompanying video directed by Spike Jonze are considered classics of 1990s house music.
